The paper proposes an algorithm for meta-learning that is applicable to a variety of different learning problems, including classification, regression, and reinforcement learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and robotics (cs.RO). However, given that the paper focuses on deep networks and their fast adaptation, it is most likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
